sentences: Johannes Hendrikus Jacob van den Berg (born 22 March 1946), better known as his stage name Harry Vanda, is a Dutch Australian musician, songwriter and record producer.
He is best known as lead guitarist of the 1960s Australian rock band the Easybeats who with fellow member George Young formed the 1970s and 1980s songwriting and record production duo Vanda & Young.
He is best known as lead guitarist of the 1960s Australian rock band the Easybeats who with fellow member George Young formed the 1970s and 1980s songwriting and record production duo Vanda & Young.
Vanda's family migrated to Australia from the Netherlands in 1963, and settled in Sydney.
section: == Early life ==

sentences: Vanda, who had been a guitarist with the Hague-based band the Starfighters, came to fame in 1964–65 as the lead guitarist of the Easybeats.
section: == Early life ==

sentences: In the same year he met rhythm guitarist George Young at the Villawood migrant hostel.
section: == Early life ==

sentences: In 2007, Australian Musician magazine selected this meeting as the most significant event in Australian pop and rock music history.
section: == Early life ==

sentences: In 1966, both Vanda and Young penned many of the Easybeats' later recordings, including their major international hit, "Friday On My Mind".
section: == Career ==

sentences: In 1966, both Vanda and Young penned many of the Easybeats' later recordings, including their major international hit, "Friday On My Mind".
section: == Career ==

sentences: After the Easybeats disbanded in 1970, Vanda & Young remained in the UK and continued their writing and performing partnership.
section: == Career ==

sentences: In 1973, Vanda and Young returned to Australia and took over as the house producers for leading independent record production company, Albert Productions, and publisher J. Albert & Son.
section: == Career ==

sentences: From 1974 onwards they enjoyed huge success in Australia and internationally, writing and producing hits for a number of popular Australian groups and solo singers, including John Paul Young, Cheetah, Stevie Wright, Ted Mulry, Rose Tattoo, the Angels, William Shakespeare, Mark Williams and, most notably, AC/DC.
section: == Career ==

sentences: In 1988 Vanda was inducted, along with George Young, into the inaugural class of the ARIA Hall of Fame.
section: == Career ==

sentences: By the late 1990s, Vanda and Young had left their longtime partnership with Albert Productions, and retired from the music industry.
section: == Career ==

sentences: However, in 2005, Harry Vanda started Flashpoint Music in Surry Hills with his producer/engineer son, Daniel Vandenberg, setting up one of Australia's premier private studios.
section: == Career ==

sentences: Vanda used a 1964 Höfner Verithin 1574 with Bigsby tremolo and 511 pickups, before switching in 1965 to a Gibson 345.

sentences: In the Easybeats, Vanda also often played a cherry-red Maton 12-string electric guitar, which he donated to the collection of Powerhouse Museum in Sydney in 1999.

sentences: Since 2009, Albert Music and APRA AMCOS have held the Vanda & Young Global Songwriting Competition, named after the musicians.
